text: #Stocks sold off on Friday with the #Dow dropping more than 10% below its October peak. All major US indices are now in #correction territory. The #USD and #Oil also fell. Here's what to expect from #markets this week: https:// invst.ly/9j9jo $ SPY $ DIA $ QQQ pic.twitter.com/CIcuDOaS08
#Dow The Dow’s 2% fall Friday is its third steepest this month. The other two declines also came a day before the stock market was set to be closed.

#Dow The blue-chip index declined nearly 500 points, putting all three major U.S. stock indexes simultaneously in correction territory—typically defined as a fall of at least 10% from a recent high—for the first time since March 2016.
